# Web app UI and redesign

When the user asks to **change the web app look**, **redesign the UI**, or work on **frontend/UI** in this project:

1. **Invoke or follow** the project skills:
   - **@frontend-design** (Anthropic) – distinctive, production-grade frontend; avoid generic AI aesthetics; bold typography, color, motion, spatial composition.
   - **@ui-ux-pro-max** – design intelligence: styles, palettes, font pairings, accessibility, touch targets, layout.

2. **Brainstorming** is available globally (**@using-superpowers** in `~/.agents/skills/`) – use it for ideation before implementing.

3. Apply both skills when implementing: pick a clear aesthetic direction, then implement with the frontend-design and ui-ux-pro-max guidelines (typography, color, accessibility, touch targets, motion).

For **backend** (e.g. `backend/server.js`, API design): no need to invoke frontend-design or ui-ux-pro-max unless the task involves API docs or developer-facing UI.
